content:
Create a remote connection using the Amazon Redshift connector to sync data from Amazon Redshift to CRM Analytics.

Before creating an Amazon Redshift connection, ensure that the Redshift cluster is SSL enabled. Create the Connection

On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection.
Click the name of the connector and click Next.
Enter the connector settings:
Connection Name
Developer Name (API name for the connection)
Description
Username
Number Of Nodes in Cluster
Schema
Cluster Node Type
JDBC URL (Your Amazon Redshift connection URL)
Password
S3 Bucket Name (Optional)

Exclude unnecessary or sensitive data from syncing to CRM Analytics with data sync filters.

To create a filter, From Data Manager, click the Connections tab.
Select the connection associated with the object to filter.
Click the name of the object to filter.
Click Data Sync Filter.
Enter the filter.
Click Save.

Note: If you expect to use excluded data in the future, use a recipe filter instead of a data sync filter.
title: Connecting Amazon Redshift to CRM Analytics
